
// This Hyperlambda code checks two conditions using an [if] statement combined with [and]. It verifies if the [has-sitemap] signal node is false and if the count of [urls] nodes is zero using [eq] and [get-count]. If both conditions are true, it sets the [has-sitemap] node to false using [set-value].
if
   and
      eq:x:@signal/*/has-sitemap
         .:bool:false
      eq
         get-count:x:@.urls/*
         .:int:0
   .lambda
      set-value:x:@.has-sitemap
         .:bool:false
